Real feeling is the last thing one looks for in two such excessively well-bred and fickle person- ages as the speakers. Their pouting and reconciliation make very pretty fooling, such as might be appropriate in the wonderful beings who people the garden land- scapes of Watteau. But where are the fever and the strong pulse of passion which, in less ethereal morta18‚ would be proper to such a theme? Had there been a real lady in the case, the tone would have been less measured, and the strophes less skilfully balanced.
